# OpenFAST output binaries are too large for git (50-100 MB each per
# scenario; ~1 GB across the M6 set) and are regenerable from the
# committed deck inputs. Run scripts/extract_openfast_fixtures.py to
# (a) re-execute OpenFAST against the inputs and (b) extract the small
# canonical CSV+JSON pairs that the M6 scenario tests consume.
*.outb

# OpenFAST checkpoint files are even larger (~350 MB per scenario)
# and exist only because OpenFAST wrote them mid-run; not needed for
# downstream consumption.
*.chkp

# MoorDyn writes a separate text output alongside the main .outb
# whenever the module is active (S4 only in our M6 set, ~1.7 MB).
# Its tension columns are merged into the canonical CSV by the
# extraction script (see _merge_moordyn_into_canonical), so the raw
# .MD.out is not needed by consumers and is regenerable from the
# committed inputs. Same policy as .outb.
*.MD.out
